<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_kom_2"
    n="2" xml:lang="os">
    <form type="lemma"><orth>kom</orth></form>
    <re><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в выражении</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">in
            the expression</note><form type="lemma"><orth>kom dæddyn</orth></form><sense><cit
                type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>соглашаться</q>
            </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>agree</q>
            </cit></sense></re>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>ældar yn læxstæ kæny, fælæ ḱyzg kom na dæddy</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>алдар умоляет ее, но девушка не дает согласия</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>Aldar is begging her, but the girl does not give consent</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III 115</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>ranyxas-banyxas fækodtoj... æmæ bony fæstagmæ Farīzety fyd kom radta</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>судили-рядили, и под конец отец Фаризет дал согласие (выдать дочь)</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>they were hashing and and rehashing, and in the end father Farizet agreed (to
                    marry off his daughter)</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>131</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>ældar yn læxstæ kæny, fælæ ḱyzg kom na dæddy</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>алдар умоляет ее, но девушка не дает согласия</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>Aldar is begging her, but the girl does not give consent</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III 115</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>ranyxas-banyxas fækodtoj... æmæ bony fæstagmæ Farīzety fyd kom radta</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>судили-рядили, и под конец отец Фаризет дал согласие (выдать дочь)</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>they were hashing and and rehashing, and in the end father Farizet agreed (to
                    marry off his daughter)</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>131</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к иран. %i*kāma-%i ‘желание’: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>kām</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
            ><lang/><w>kāmak</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="ru">(из пехл.) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from Pahlavi)
                </note><w>kʼamk</w><gloss><q>желание</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="xcl"><w/><gloss><q>воля</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                ><w>k’amim</w><gloss><q>я хочу</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>*kām-(kʼm-)</w><gloss><q>хотеть</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><w/><gloss><q>любить</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>kama-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
            ><lang/><w>kāma-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>kāma-</w><gloss><q>желание</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>любовь</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Сюда и глагол <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_komyn"/> ‘уступать’, ‘соглашаться’ q. v. — Выражение %ikommæ
        kæsyn%i ‘повиноваться’, буквально „смотреть в рот“, связано не с этим, а с предыдущим словом
            (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_kom"/>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                /><biblScope>45</biblScope></bibl>.—-<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to Iranian %i*kāma-%i ‘wish’: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>kām</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
            ><lang/><w>kāmak</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="ru">(из пехл.) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from Pahlavi)
                </note><w>kʼamk</w><gloss><q>wish</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>will</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                ><w>k’amim</w><gloss><q>I want</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>*kām-(kʼm-)</w><gloss><q>to want</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><w/><gloss><q>to love</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>kama-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
            ><lang/><w>kāma-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>kāma-</w><gloss><q>wish</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>love</q></gloss></mentioned>, . It is related to a verb <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_komyn"/> ‘to give in’, ‘to agree’ q. v. — The expression
        %ikommæ kæsyn%i ‘to obey’, literally „to look into the mouth“, is connected not with this
        word, but with the previous one (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_kom"/>).%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>45</biblScope></bibl>.—-<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
